# CODEOWNERS — enforce review on security-sensitive surfaces.
#
# The Atlas Worker has a full-access R2 binding to the shadow-atlas
# bucket (Cloudflare R2 bindings don't support a wrangler.toml
# read-only flag as of 2026-05). The Worker code only calls
# .get()/.head(), but a malicious or accidental commit introducing
# .put/.delete/.list would have full bucket-write blast radius.
# Mandatory review on these paths is the practical mitigation until
# Cloudflare ships per-binding read-only scoping.
workers/atlas/         @ejmockler
